<subSubSection id="DD20662A2613B62BB15F31C3A4A449CF" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" type="distribution and taxonomic notes">
<paragraph id="E5B3AC0AB9CBF2AADAA2B406171D7195" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">Distribution and taxonomic notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="46D0218B0AB2E05FEB83B96A02F4C656" pageId="3" pageNumber="126">
<taxonomicName id="A873261A01656446C736E25FC7BB1DAD" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. grisea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="grisea">Zygaena rhadamanthus grisea</taxonomicName>
has a wide distribution in south-eastern and southern-central France, ranging from Alpes-de-Haute-Provence and Hautes-Alpes to 
<normalizedToken id="8C47A73264FCCBBE85ED78DE54B27B28" originalValue="Isère">Isere</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken id="EA3B2ABB66321BB5740B1C2A4CEA4BB3" originalValue="Drôme">Drome</normalizedToken>
, 
<normalizedToken id="E79EEB41CF40E3109208532DF8559ECF" originalValue="Ardèche">Ardeche</normalizedToken>
, Vaucluse, Aveyron, Lot and 
<normalizedToken id="50D7B655756A45089DDB516C45E9AEBC" originalValue="Lozère">Lozere</normalizedToken>
. Based on phenotype (and geography - 
<taxonomicName id="590550FAF124982102062C4E147B1ECB" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. cleui" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="cleui">Zygaena rhadamanthus cleui</taxonomicName>
cannot be recognised as valid because its location is within the distributional range of 
<taxonomicName id="69B0F646412176BADDD34CC04C9FD49D" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. grisea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="grisea">Zygaena rhadamanthus grisea</taxonomicName>
), we see no justification for 
<bibRefCitation id="C80CC920E88BF4C77D0D18FAA42CA32E" author="Leraut, P" journalOrPublisher="NAP Editions, Verrieres-le Buisson" pageId="7" pageNumber="130" title="Volume 3: Moths of Europe, Zygaenids, Pyralids 1 and Brachodids." year="2012">
<normalizedToken id="3AA0533B00C5EE13DFD7ADACD3C5A70F" originalValue="Leraut’s">Leraut's</normalizedToken>
(2012
</bibRefCitation>
: 98) reinstatement of 
<taxonomicName id="44F43ED697C9A49375E813472C052C4C" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. cleui" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="cleui">Zygaena rhadamanthus cleui</taxonomicName>
as a valid subspecies under which he placed 
<taxonomicName id="ED8C55EB1015C43DD5E7E8FBFA3B04C5" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. aragonia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="aragonia">Zygaena rhadamanthus aragonia</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="D8FD84A2DF21B37A77C54C863D6FC1E2" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. aurargentea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="aurargentea">Zygaena rhadamanthus aurargentea</taxonomicName>
as synonyms (see also below). Even in the original description, Dujardin compared 
<taxonomicName id="D8C9259001E39415C6675B361298C4FE" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. cleui" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="cleui">Zygaena rhadamanthus cleui</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="2683E47166219968EE8B268AB5C94C87" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. grisea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="grisea">Zygaena rhadamanthus grisea</taxonomicName>
, stating that the forewing ground colour was similar. Consequently, it is here reinstated as a synonym (syn. rev.) of 
<taxonomicName id="8E0C926D78BAE09D1105D07398731446" class="Insecta" family="Zygaenidae" genus="Zygaena" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zygaena rhadamanthus subsp. grisea" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="126" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="rhadamanthus" subSpecies="grisea">Zygaena rhadamanthus grisea</taxonomicName>
, as placed by 
<bibRefCitation id="D7D83A55F3DE88E9B502E794B7A03597" author="Hofmann, A" journalOrPublisher="Harley Books, Colchester" pageId="7" pageNumber="130" title="A systematic Catalogue of the Zygaeninae (Lepidoptera: Zygaenidae)." year="1996">Hofmann and Tremewan (1996</bibRefCitation>
: 131).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
